Package ui

The package that has to do with the user interface for Cards Against Humanity.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Animated
    An superinterface for interfaces that contain methods for animating objects.
    Growable
    A group of methods for classes of objects that are can grow.
    Movable
    A collection of methods used by objects that move.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AboutDialog
    Shows the "about" information.
    AddComputerPlayer
    A JDialog that allows users to add computer players to a game of Cards Against Humanity.
    AddHumanPlayer
    A class of object that represents a JDialog that adds a human player to a game of cards against humanity.
    AddPlayer
    A class of object that represents a dialog that askes the user which type of player they would like to add to a game of Cards Against Humanity.
    BlackCard
    A class of object that represents a Black CAH card in the form of a panel.
    BlankBlackCard
    A UICard that represents a blank black card that represents the back of a black card.
    BlankWhiteCard
    A UICard that shows a blank white card to represent the back of a white card.
    CAH_Cards
    A class of object that represents the layered pane that contains information about a players statistics.
    CAH_Frame
    A class of object that represents the frame that contains Cards against humanity.
    CAH_LoadGame
    A class of object that represents the panel that shows up when a user decides to load an old saved game.
    CAH_Netplay
    A class of object that represents the panel that will come up to allow a player to start up netplay.
    CAH_NewGame
    The panel that creates the menu for a new CAH game.
    CAH_Stats
    A class of object that represents the layered pane that contains information about a players statistics.
    CAH_Users
    The panel that allows people to register as a user.
    CardInfoPanel
    A class of object that represents the JPanel that is seen below the Card in the Cards panel.
    ExitDialog
    A JDialog that warns people before they exit the application.
    Expansion1Options
    The options for expansion 1.
    GamePane
    The layered pane that contains the game.
    ListScrConstraints
    A class of object that represents the scroll constraints of a JList.
    MTimerListener
    A class of object that represents a timer listener designed for dealing with movement animations.
    PlayerPanel
    A class of object that represents the panel where a players information is displayed
    RemovePlayerDialog
    A dialog that warns people when they remove a player and asks them to confirm the players removal.
    RulesHelpDialog
    A class of object that represents a dialog box that comes up when the user hits the rules menu item.
    RulesPanel
    A class of object that represents the panel that contains information about Cards Against Humanity's rules.
    SmallWhiteCard  
    TimerListener
    An abstract class of object that represents a class of object that listens for action events caused by Timers.
    UICard
    A superclass for BlackCard and WhiteCard.
    UserPanel
    A JPanel that shows a user's information.
    UserPanelEdit
    A panel that allows editing of user information.
    WhiteCard
    A class of object that represents a white CAH card.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Animated.AnimationSpeed
    An enumeration of different animation speeds.
    CAH_Frame.screens
    A list of the different screens that there are.
